LG has announced the launch of its K10 smartphone in South Africa, at a recommended retail price of R3,899. The K-series refresh was unveiled at CES in Las Vegas, with the new mid-range devices designed to bring technologies from LG’s premium smartphones to the mass market. This includes features like the 120-degree wide angle front camera lens and the rear fingerprint scanner. The specifications of LG’s upcoming K smartphones are summarised in the table below.